<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: PROPERTY MANAGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newport Beach-based Donahue Schriber, a commercial real estate developer and 
manager, has named Geoff Fults leasing representative for The Promenade, a 
regional shopping center in Woodland Hills. 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: The Angeles Girl Scout Council's elite Green &amp; White Select 
Committee will bestow its highest honors on Lilly Lee and Howard White at its 
seventh annual fund-raising dinner. Lee, chairperson of Lilly Enterprises Inc. 
and Lilly Property Management Co., will receive the Grace Award, which is given 
to a community leader for exemplifying the Girl Scout values. White, managing 
director of finance at Arthur Anderson &amp; Co., will be given the Good Scout 
Salute, which honors a corporation or individual for its dedication and support 
of the Girl Scout programs and its goals. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Builders/Developers 
</P>
<P>
Wheatland Construction Co. has announced a realignment in its management ranks 
by naming Brad Gorman, president, and Rex Wheatland, chairman of the board. 
Located in Whittier, the firm specializes in commercial and industrial 
construction, including dams, electrical power plants and medical facilities. 
</P>
<P>
Charles E. Harger has joined Maguire Thomas Partners as senior vice president 
of construction. Harger will be in charge of all the firm's development 
projects nationwide. The L.A.-based company's major downtown projects include 
First Interstate World Center, Southern California Gas Center and Wells Fargo 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
Ken Baumgartner has been promoted to senior vice president for acquisition and 
planning at McMillin Communities. The company is located in National City (part 
of greater San Diego) and specializes in the move-up housing market. 
</P>
<P>
Jeanette Engle has joined Ahmanson Commercial Development Co. as senior vice 
president and chief financial officer. The Los Angeles-based company is a 
subsidiary of Home Savings of America and has projects in the Los Angeles, San 
Diego, Oakland and Chicago areas. 
</P>
<P>
Raffi Cohen Industries of Los Angeles has named Brooke E. Goranson vice 
president, director of leasing. She will be responsible for marketing and 
leasing programs for Figueroa Plaza, One Civic Center and Figueroa Tower office 
projects in the downtown area. 
</P>
<P>
Ronald H. Roberts has been named vice president of River Edge Development Co. 
Inc. and project manager for Oxnard Town Center, a mixed-used project in 
Ventura County. Roberts has been involved with the Oxnard project for over five 
years. 
</P>
<P>
Pardee Construction Co. has promoted Michael V. McGee to vice president, 
project manager of its Riverside County development operations. Working from 
the Rancho California office, he will oversee planning, processing, approvals 
and development coordination of the firm's residential, commercial and 
industrial projects. 
</P>
<P>
James E. Whalen has been named vice president of Newland California, a San 
Diego-based land development firm. Whalen will oversee Newland's industrial and 
office projects in Sorrento Hills and Poway. His duties will include planning, 
liaison with the city of San Diego, marketing, coordination of broker 
activities, as well as establishing design guidelines and review of 
architectural submissions. 
</P>
<P>
Maguire Thomas Partners has announced two promotions, both to the position of 
vice president: Daniel R. Kingsley and Charles J. Tillotson. Los Angeles-based 
Maguire Thomas specializes in the development of institutional-quality office 
and mixed-use projects. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Beach-based home builder J.M. Peters Co. has promoted Greg R. Petersen 
to vice president-controller. He will handle all financial reporting. The firm 
is building homes for the move-up market throughout the Southland. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Cullinan has been appointed vice president of sales and marketing at Desert 
Horizons Inc., developer of the Desert Horizons Country Club in Indian Wells. 
</P>
<P>
The new position of director of finance for Newport Beach-based Manning Co. has 
been filled by Scott Woodside. He will be handling all accounting and finance 
functions, overseeing joint-venture relationships, construction lending and 
individual job costs. Manning specializes in single-family detached move-up 
home development in the Inland Empire and the Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
Valerie Copen has moved up to director of purchasing at Richmond American 
Homes. She has been with the firm five years. Headquartered in Irvine, the 
company focuses on residential building. 
</P>
<P>
John W. Fulbright has joined Kaufman &amp; Broad of San Diego as director of 
forward planning. The firm is a subsidiary of Kaufman &amp; Broad Home Corp., a 
home builder. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Mortgage/Title Firms 
</P>
<P>
Bankers Mutual, a mortgage banking corporation, has promoted Trent D. Brooks to 
senior vice president. Headquartered in Newport Beach, the company specializes 
in funding large multifamily loans secured by apartment projects in the West. 
</P>
<P>
Theresa Canady has joined the business development department of Gateways 
Title's Inland Empire office in Colton. As major account manager, she will 
handle the commercial and industrial accounts in Riverside and San Bernardino 
counties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
